\section{Goals}
Although different technologies %were developed% have been developed to answer the challenges of DNA sequencing, the actual goal of designers is to constantly improve DNA micro-arrays to ensure a better understanding of the DNA molecule. Thus, the idea is to reduce the size of the sensing system by improving the scalability without compromises on the robustness and the sensitivity of the device.

The ISFET pH-sensor provide a promising technology for the future of DNA sequencing. %The MOSFET is an electrical structure with a gate as a reference electrode and a insulating layer. % %Due to its MOSFET electrical structure with the gate as a reference electrode and an insulating layer% %It is sensitive to pH which modulate its output response.% Nevertheless, this chemical transistor suffers from nonidealities such as chemical noise, drift, trapped charges and classical MOSFET defects. The idea of this thesis is to focus on DNA micro-array using pH-sensing systems such as ISFETs. However, we have seen that ISFETs present passivation and chemical capacitances which affect the behavior of the device.

It has also been demonstrated that the hexagonal tilling is the densest way to arrange circles in two dimensions. In this idea, an hexagonal organization of ISFETs would be beneficial to improve the packing density of micro array. Moreover, hexagonal transistors are part of a category called enclosed-gate transistors which present interesting properties in term of speed, strain capacitance and matching. Applied to ISFETs, these properties could also improve the pH-detection. Consequently it would be interesting to focus on hexagonal transistors applied to pH-sensing.

In the end, because the ISFET sensor must be embedded into an entire system which perform pH detection with the best sensitivity,the next part focus on specific implementation of ISFET in CMOS technology. %This part% The following part will discuss of a new ISFET topology and its use in a integrated micro-array. Then, the latest consideration%s %about EGT are developed as well as the model to describe such structures.


